{
  "page": "Valemen",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Anders_Finer_jonsman.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/6/6e/Anders_Finer_jonsman.jpg/350px-Anders_Finer_jonsman.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"290\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/6/6e/Anders_Finer_jonsman.jpg/525px-Anders_Finer_jonsman.jpg 1.5x, /images/6/6e/Anders_Finer_jonsman.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Anders_Finer_jonsman.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A man loyal to Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jon_Arryn\" title=\"Jon Arryn\">Jon Arryn</a>, by Anders Finer © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Valemen</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_arrival_of_the_andals.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_arrival_of_the_andals.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> are natives of the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn\" title=\"Vale of Arryn\">Vale of Arryn</a>, an eastern region of the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Ethnicity\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Ethnicity</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Culture\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Culture</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Religion\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Religion</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Customs\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Customs</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Ethnicity\">Ethnicity</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Valemen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Ethnicity\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn_(valley)\" title=\"Vale of Arryn (valley)\">Vale</a> and the <a href=\"/index.php/Mountains_of_the_Moon\" title=\"Mountains of the Moon\">Mountains of the Moon</a> were settled in antiquity by the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Men\" title=\"First Men\">First Men</a>, who established numerous petty kingdoms in the region over many centuries.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The Vale was where the <a href=\"/index.php/Andals\" title=\"Andals\">Andals</a> landed when they began their <a href=\"/index.php/Coming_of_the_Andals\" title=\"Coming of the Andals\">invasion of Westeros</a>. Utilizing <a href=\"/index.php/Armament\" title=\"Armament\">armament</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Iron\" title=\"Iron\">iron</a>, the Andals defeated the <a href=\"/index.php/Bronze\" title=\"Bronze\">bronze</a>-wielding First Men.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_arrival_of_the_andals.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_arrival_of_the_andals.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Ruling <a href=\"/index.php/House_Arryn\" title=\"House Arryn\">House Arryn</a> descends from one of the oldest and purest lines of Andal nobility.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragotappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragotappendix.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Some of the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Men\" title=\"First Men\">First Men</a> submitted to the conquerors and accepted the <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Faith of the Seven</a>, while others fled into the mountains and became the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_mountain_clans\" title=\"Vale mountain clans\">mountain clans</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> considered savage by <a href=\"/index.php/Lowlander\" title=\"Lowlander\">lowlanders</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale:_house_arryn.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_vale:_house_arryn.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Some <a href=\"/index.php/Sistermen\" title=\"Sistermen\">Sistermen</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Three_Sisters\" title=\"Three Sisters\">Three Sisters</a> have webbing between their hands and feet, which they call the mark.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Culture\">Culture</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Valemen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Culture\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Religion\">Religion</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Valemen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Religion\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:A_message_for_the_bloody_gate_by_steves3511-d8n7dsh.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/73/A_message_for_the_bloody_gate_by_steves3511-d8n7dsh.jpg/350px-A_message_for_the_bloody_gate_by_steves3511-d8n7dsh.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"233\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/73/A_message_for_the_bloody_gate_by_steves3511-d8n7dsh.jpg/525px-A_message_for_the_bloody_gate_by_steves3511-d8n7dsh.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/73/A_message_for_the_bloody_gate_by_steves3511-d8n7dsh.jpg/700px-A_message_for_the_bloody_gate_by_steves3511-d8n7dsh.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:A_message_for_the_bloody_gate_by_steves3511-d8n7dsh.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A message for the <a href=\"/index.php/Bloody_Gate\" title=\"Bloody Gate\">Bloody Gate</a>, by Stephen Najarian ©</div></div></div>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Faith_of_the_Seven\" title=\"Faith of the Seven\">Faith of the Seven</a>, brought by the <a href=\"/index.php/Andals\" title=\"Andals\">Andals</a>, is the predominant religion among <a href=\"/index.php/Lowland\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Lowland\">lowland</a> Valemen. Carvings of seven-pointed stars and double-bladed axes, left by the Andal conquerors, can be found in the <a href=\"/index.php/Fingers\" title=\"Fingers\">Fingers</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Mountains_of_the_Moon\" title=\"Mountains of the Moon\">Mountains of the Moon</a>, and at the <a href=\"/index.php/Giant%27s_Lance\" title=\"Giant&#39;s Lance\">Giant's Lance</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_norvos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_free_cities:_norvos.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/House_Arryn\" title=\"House Arryn\">House Arryn</a> fostered learning in <a href=\"/index.php/Septry\" title=\"Septry\">septries</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Sept\" title=\"Sept\">septs</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale:_house_arryn.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_vale:_house_arryn.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_mountain_clans\" title=\"Vale mountain clans\">mountain clansmen</a>, however, do not follow the Seven.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Customs\">Customs</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Valemen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Customs\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The rich soil of the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn_(valley)\" title=\"Vale of Arryn (valley)\">Vale</a> allows the Valemen to grow fine wheat, barley, corn, pumpkins, and fruits.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Some consider the <a href=\"/index.php/Knights_of_the_Vale\" title=\"Knights of the Vale\">knights of the Vale</a> to be the finest of the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/index.php/Winged_Knight\" title=\"Winged Knight\">Winged Knight</a> is a legendary figure in the Vale.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Sister%27s_stew\" title=\"Sister&#39;s stew\">Sister's stew</a> is popular in the <a href=\"/index.php/Three_Sisters\" title=\"Three Sisters\">Three Sisters</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> Some <a href=\"/index.php/Sistermen\" title=\"Sistermen\">Sistermen</a> use false lights to cause unsuspecting ships to wreck.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Unlike the feudal <a href=\"/index.php/Lowlander\" title=\"Lowlander\">lowlanders</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_mountain_clans\" title=\"Vale mountain clans\">clansmen</a> who live in the <a href=\"/index.php/Mountains_of_the_Moon\" title=\"Mountains of the Moon\">Mountains of the Moon</a> have a more egalitarian<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> but also more violent society.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot62.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot62.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Bastardy\" title=\"Bastardy\">Bastards</a> of noble origin raised in the Vale can be given the surname Stone.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Valemen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Rise_of_the_Mountain_Clans_Skysoul_Visual_Art_Studios.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/f/fe/Rise_of_the_Mountain_Clans_Skysoul_Visual_Art_Studios.png/350px-Rise_of_the_Mountain_Clans_Skysoul_Visual_Art_Studios.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"237\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/fe/Rise_of_the_Mountain_Clans_Skysoul_Visual_Art_Studios.png/525px-Rise_of_the_Mountain_Clans_Skysoul_Visual_Art_Studios.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/fe/Rise_of_the_Mountain_Clans_Skysoul_Visual_Art_Studios.png/700px-Rise_of_the_Mountain_Clans_Skysoul_Visual_Art_Studios.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Rise_of_the_Mountain_Clans_Skysoul_Visual_Art_Studios.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Vale_mountain_clans\" title=\"Vale mountain clans\">Mountain clansmen</a> of the Vale, by Skysoul Visual Art Studios © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Isolated from the rest of <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a> by its <a href=\"/index.php/Mountains_of_the_Moon\" title=\"Mountains of the Moon\">towering mountains</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn\" title=\"Vale of Arryn\">Vale</a> proved the perfect ground for the <a href=\"/index.php/Andals\" title=\"Andals\">Andals</a> to carve out their first kingdoms in this new land. The <a href=\"/index.php/First_Men\" title=\"First Men\">First Men</a>, who were there before the Andals, fought these seaborne conquerors stubbornly, but the Vale was but thinly peopled in those days, and they soon found themselves outnumbered in every fight.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_vale.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn_(valley)\" title=\"Vale of Arryn (valley)\">It</a> stretched before them to the misty east, a tranquil land of rich black soil, wide slow-moving rivers, and hundreds of small lakes that shone like mirrors in the sun, protected on all sides by <a href=\"/index.php/Mountains_of_the_Moon\" title=\"Mountains of the Moon\">its sheltering peaks</a>. Wheat and corn and barley grew high in its fields, and even in <a href=\"/index.php/Highgarden\" title=\"Highgarden\">Highgarden</a> the pumpkins were no larger nor the fruit any sweeter than here.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot34.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>That was the trouble with the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_mountain_clans\" title=\"Vale mountain clans\">clans</a>; they had an absurd notion that every man's voice should be heard in council, so they argued about everything, endlessly.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Petyr_Baelish\" title=\"Petyr Baelish\">Littlefinger</a> holds the <a href=\"/index.php/Eyrie\" title=\"Eyrie\">Eyrie</a> now ... though not for long. The lords of the <a href=\"/index.php/Vale_of_Arryn\" title=\"Vale of Arryn\">Vale</a> are not the sort to bend their knees to some upjumped jackanapes whose only skill is counting <a href=\"/index.php/Currency\" title=\"Currency\">coppers</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Randyll_Tarly\" title=\"Randyll Tarly\">Randyll Tarly</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Brienne_Tarth\" title=\"Brienne Tarth\">Brienne Tarth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Godric_Borrell\" title=\"Godric Borrell\">Godric's</a> forebears had been <a href=\"/index.php/Pirate\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pirate\">pirate</a> kings until the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\">Starks</a> came down on them with <a href=\"/index.php/Rape_of_the_Three_Sisters\" title=\"Rape of the Three Sisters\">fire and sword</a>. These days the <a href=\"/index.php/Sistermen\" title=\"Sistermen\">Sistermen</a> left open piracy to <a href=\"/index.php/Salladhor_Saan\" title=\"Salladhor Saan\">Salladhor Saan</a> and his ilk and confined themselves to wrecking. The beacons that burned along the shores of the <a href=\"/index.php/Three_Sisters\" title=\"Three Sisters\">Three Sisters</a> were supposed to warn of shoals and reefs and rocks and lead the way to safety, but on stormy nights and foggy ones, some Sistermen would use false lights to draw unwary captains to their doom.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd9.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Davos_Seaworth\" title=\"Davos Seaworth\">Davos Seaworth</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Valemen&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_arrival_of_the_andals.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafancient_history:_the_arrival_of_the_